        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "Looking for a `.chunks` attribute could make sense.  Sometimes the chunksize that makes sense for storage is more fine than makes sense for computation.  So far we have stuck to a \"force users to think about chunksizes rather than guess\" philosophy.  I find this straightforward but I could be convinced otherwise.  Any thoughts @jcrist or @shoyer ?",
